      "Based on the web search results, here's what I found about Claude Code updates and features around February 2026:\n\n## Claude Code Updates - February 2026\n\n### Major Release: Claude Code Security Module\n- **February 20, 2026**: Anthropic officially released the **Claude Code Security** module for the web version\n- This security-enhanced tool combines automated scanning with human-like analysis capabilities\n- Can identify business logic defects, access control issues, and other security vulnerabilities\n\n### Recent Version Updates (Leading into February 2026)\n\n**Claude Code 2.1.x Series** (January 2026):\n- **2.1.1**: Quick hotfix release\n- **2.1.0**: Major \"backward-compatible feature enhancement\" version\n- **2.0.76**: Transition version\n\nThe update from 2.0.76 to 2.1.0 included **1,096 commits**, indicating a substantial update. Key features included:\n\n### Key Features Added:\n1. **Skills Hot Reload** - Improves development and debugging efficiency\n2. **Multi-language Response Configuration** - Support for languages like Simplified Chinese\n3. **Shift+Enter Support** - Input line breaks without additional configuration\n4. **Enhanced Skill Functions** - New capabilities added\n5. **Hooks Support** - Can add hooks directly in Agent and Skill frontmatter\n6. **Tool Permission Wildcards** - Wildcard support for tool permissions\n7. **Improved Error Handling** - Agent no longer terminates when user denies tool usage\n\n### Related Model Updates:\n- **February 6, 2026**: Anthropic released **Claude Opus 4.6**, their first flagship model with 1 million token context window testing capabilities\n- Improvements in long-context querying, reasoning, and planning\n\n### Installation/Update Commands:\n- Global install: `npm update -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code`\n- Specific version: `npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code@2.1.1`\n- Check version: `claude --version`\n\nThe search results indicate that Claude Code continued its rapid evolution in early 2026, transitioning from a pure command-line tool to a more mature development platform with enhanced security, better multi-language support, and improved agent capabilities."
